---
// THE LAB — six floating doors, one quiet room. V3.2 (2026-07-21): themed
// (dark is home — /theme.js sets data-theme pre-paint; the var block below
// carries every paper) and grounded — each door is data-zg-tight: zero
// wander, a tug that rubberbands home. The engine owns each door's OUTER
// transform (inline, every frame), so all cosmetics — border, radius,
// background, entrance rise, hover scale — live on the .din inner wrapper
// where they compose instead of fight. Percent homes park the doors via
// CSS until the engine boots; under reduced motion it never does, and the
// parked layout IS the page.
//
// Five doors navigate (through the curtain, flooded with the LIVE --ink so
// it reads on dark paper); the sixth, WIP, is a span — it drags like the
// rest and a true click cycles its color, but it goes nowhere. All five
// targets autoReveal, so the covered flag is never cleared here: it rides
// through and peels itself on arrival.
---

<html lang="en">
